The paper deals with building models of robot environments using a mobile robot equipped with a laser range finder, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm presented in the paper involves learning object models using shape templates, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of an EM algorithm for learning shape parameters and a Bayesian model selection algorithm suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with modeling non-stationary environments, which could also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
